the scenery. Whatever plants survive the firestorms will now be starved for sunlight, as global

07:13.440 --> 07:20.800
photosynthesis is temporarily shut down. Within days, temperatures crash as much as 25 degrees Celsius.

07:21.680 --> 07:27.840
The oceans were especially hard hit. The lack of sunlight killed over 90 percent of plankton,

